== Executive Summary ==

**Document Type**: Scientific Statement (Expert Consensus Review)
**Source Credibility**: VERY HIGH
**Overall Assessment**: WELL-SUPPORTED with IMPORTANT NUANCES

The AHA Scientific Statement represents a comprehensive, expert-reviewed synthesis of current evidence on alcohol and cardiovascular disease. It represents a **significant shift** from previous guidance by challenging the long-held belief that moderate alcohol consumption provides cardiovascular protection.

**Key Finding**: The available evidence suggests no risk to possible risk reduction when alcohol is consumed in low amounts (such as no more than 1 to 2 drinks a day) in regard to coronary artery disease, stroke, sudden death, and possibly heart failure. However, newer methodologies (Mendelian randomization) have challenged whether even this modest potential benefit is real.

