== Context: Evolution of Scientific Understanding ==

=== Previous Understanding (Pre-2020) ===

* "French Paradox" suggesting wine protects heart health
* J-shaped curve widely accepted
* Some guidelines suggested moderate drinking might be cardioprotective

=== Current Understanding (2024-2025) ===

When the scientists conducted such genetic analyses of samples taken from participants, they found that individuals with genetic variants that predicted higher alcohol consumption were indeed more likely to consume greater amounts of alcohol, and more likely to have hypertension and coronary artery disease.

Study type determines whether research finds alcohol reduces IHD risk or is unrelated, arguing for new approaches to settle this critical debate.

=== Key Shift ===

A review of the evidence in 2025 produced a more cautious summary. Prior to the new methodologies, protection against coronary artery disease from moderate alcohol use was derived from many observational studies.

